<p>Haxeflixel is available to use on Linux, Mac or Windows. You will need to have <a target="_blank" href="http://www.haxe.org/"> Haxe 3 </a> and <a href="https://openfl.org">OpenFL</a><a target="_blank" href="http://www.haxenme.org/"> </a> installed and working.</p>

<p>We recomend you use <a target="_blank" href="http://haxe.org/doc/haxelib/using_haxelib%20">Haxelib</a> with the following command:</p>

<div><div class="syntaxhighlighter nogutter  bash" id="highlighter_628841"><div class="toolbar"><span><a class="toolbar_item command_help help" href="#">?</a></span></div><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"><tbody><tr><td class="code"><div class="container"><div class="line number1 index0 alt2"><code class="bash plain">haxelib </code><code class="bash functions">install</code> <code class="bash plain">flixel</code></div></div></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>

<p>To download the latest stable code use master branch, or this link to the zip:</p>

<p><a href="https://github.com/HaxeFlixel/flixel/archive/master.zip" class="btn btn-large">Download Zip</a></p>

<p>If you need help setting this up, please see the <a target="_self" href="/wiki/getting-started">Getting Started </a> article.</p>

<p>We also recommend users inspect the <a href="http://haxeflixel.com/demos">Demos</a> to see Flixel features in use.</p>

<p>The <a href="http://haxeflixel.com/wiki">wiki</a> and <a href="http://haxeflixel.com/forum">forums</a> provide the main source of community created documentation, support and resources.</p>

<p>For advanced Developers the source code is available and open for contributions on <a href="https://github.com/HaxeFlixel/flixel">github</a>, bleeding edge code is on the dev branch;</p>
